The paper proposes a new nonparametric choice model for customer behavior, which involves decision trees and probability distributions. This approach falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG), as well as decision making and game theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses the use of optimization algorithms for estimating the model, which relates to optimization and control (cs.MA) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper applies the model to real transaction data, which falls under the category of electronic commerce (cs.EC).
